  <title>HPE Helion Development Platform 2.0: Testing</title>
  <body>
    <p>Each of the tech stacks and frameworks has conventions for supporting unit testing. </p>
    <p>The HPE Helion Code Engine looks for specific files in the root directory of the project. The
      specific file found will determine how the project is built and tested.</p><note>Only one of these files is
      expected to exist in the project root directory. The behavior is undefined in the presence of
      multiple files.</note>
    
    <section><title>Java Projects</title><dl>
        <dlentry>
          <dt>pom.xml</dt>
          <dd>Build: <codeph>mvn -Dmaven.test.skip=true package</codeph>
          </dd>
          <dd>Test: <codeph>mvn test</codeph></dd>
        </dlentry>
        <dlentry>
          <dt>gradle.build</dt>
          <dd>Build: <codeph>gradle build -x test</codeph></dd>
          <dd>Test: <codeph>gradle test</codeph></dd>
        </dlentry>
        <dlentry>
          <dt>gradlew</dt>
          <dd>Build: <codeph></codeph></dd>
          <dd>Test: <codeph>gradlew test</codeph></dd>
        </dlentry>
      </dl> 
 </section>
    <section><title>Python projects</title><dl>
      <dlentry>
        <dt>tox.ini</dt>
        <dd>Build: <codeph>python setup.py install</codeph></dd>
        <dd>Test: <codeph>tox</codeph></dd>
      </dlentry><dlentry>
        <dt>setup.py</dt>
        <dd>Build: <codeph>python setup.py install</codeph></dd>
        <dd>Test: <codeph>python setup.py test</codeph></dd>
      </dlentry>
    </dl> </section>
    <section><title>NodeJS Projects</title> <dl>
      <dlentry>
        <dt></dt>
        <dd>Build: <codeph>npm install</codeph></dd>
        <dd>Test: <codeph>npm test</codeph></dd>
      </dlentry>
    </dl></section>
  </body>
